Vice President Kamala Harris met with Prime Minister Han Duck-soo of the Republic of Korea (ROK) in Tokyo, Japan. They emphasized the importance of the U.S.-ROK Alliance in maintaining peace, stability, and prosperity in the Indo-Pacific and globally. They condemned the recent ballistic missile launch by North Korea and pledged to collaborate in addressing the threats posed by North Korea's nuclear and missile programs. They also discussed their shared efforts to combat the climate crisis, including investments in clean energy. The Vice President acknowledged the ROK's concerns regarding tax incentives for electric vehicles under the Inflation Reduction Act and promised continued consultation. Additionally, they discussed strengthening economic partnership, particularly in advanced technology, semiconductors, and space cooperation.